law.text:
As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Board" means the county board of assessment appeals;
"Department" means the Department of Revenue;
"Taxpayer" means any person made liable by law to file a return or pay a tax;
"Real property" includes all lands within this state and improvements thereon;
"Personal property" includes every species and character of property, tangible and intangible, other than real property; and
"County" shall also mean a charter county government;
"Fiscal court" shall also mean the legislative body of a charter county government; and
"County judge/executive" shall also mean the chief executive officer of a charter county government.
